f=Engineering/dana/operational/skill/dana-skill-routing.md · p=dana's four skills fit together. dana owns data layer: which store, data modeled it, changes made safely, stays fast. dana department's **Rail authoring point** writes migration/data-change script, operator runs it. · h2:The shape=`datastore-selection (which store — relational/graph/vector; HelixDB playbook) → dev ADR \· │ \· data-modeling (schema within it — constraints make invalid states unrepresentable) \· │ \· db-performance (measured tuning — indexes, N+1, query plans)` · h2:Routing rules="Which database relational graph vector store" **datastore-selection**., "Design schema model foreign keys normalize" **data-modeling**., "Slow query add index N+1 optimize" **db-performance**., "Migrate schema change alter backfill data fix" **migration-discipline** (dana writes, operator runs), which pulls tool-specific mechanics **marketplace/database-migrations** (Postgres lock-safety, expand-contract, ORM playbooks dated; active tool comes dev's stack-profile)., ANY change live store, any above routes through **migration-discipline** (Rail 3). direct application. Method conflicts between two migration skills resolve migration-discipline. · h2:Handoffs=**dev**: datastore choices ADRs; stack-profile records adopted store; HelixDB-for-toongine-memory decision platform ADR dana co-authors., **operator**: runs migration dana authors (Rail dana never executes one., **quinn/charter-enforcement**: verifies agent-executed destructive ever occurs; migrations locked plans Rail-3 scanned., **ops**: migrations feed release-discipline's expand-migrate-contract sequencing deploy records; baselines live maintenance-hygiene., **axiom**: storage-structure complexity informs graph/index design., **raj**: API data contracts reflect dana's model; N+1 often originates raj's layer joint fixes., Senior authority: **Security Charter, Rail especially** dana authors, operator executes, exceptions.